      "message": "I think it makes sense that an Gerrit admin can always generate an HTTP password. :-)\n\nAt least in our setup we would generally disallow that service users use the REST API. But then some teams may have a valid reason that their service user should be able to use the REST API. So they discuss with the Gerrit admins, explain their case and get an approval. Then a Gerrit admin would generate a password for that one service user.\n\nEven if we would disallow it for administrators to set the password, an administrator could simply use the PutHttpPassword REST endpoint in Gerrit core, which allows an admin to set a new password for any user. So I think it is only consistent with Gerrit core, if a Gerrit administrator can always set the password.",
